                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=doctorrock83",
                        "name": "doctorrock83",
                        "displayName": "julien PAULI",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "->closeConnection() should (really) close the connection, but take care that every further call to any method that needs the database, will re-open it automatically",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=doctorrock83",
                        "name": "doctorrock83",
                        "displayName": "julien PAULI",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-08-22T03:02:36.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-08-22T03:02:36.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/23576",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=conradwt",
                        "name": "conradwt",
                        "displayName": "Conrad Taylor",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Hi, the issue that I'm seeing that a connection is being created and remains open everytime I invoke the code.  Thus, \n\n$database->closeConnection();\n\ndoes nothing in the above code snippet.  Is this the correct functionality?\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=conradwt",
                        "name": "conradwt",
                        "displayName": "Conrad Taylor",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-08-22T03:21:35.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-08-22T03:21:35.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/23578",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=doctorrock83",
                        "name": "doctorrock83",
                        "displayName": "julien PAULI",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "It is. closeConnection() just destroyes phisically the connection like PHP does at the end of the script.\nSo on your exemple, your closeConnection() line is not needed",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=doctorrock83",
                        "name": "doctorrock83",
                        "displayName": "julien PAULI",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-08-22T03:34:34.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-08-22T03:34:34.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/23580",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=conradwt",
                        "name": "conradwt",
                        "displayName": "Conrad Taylor",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Hi, I reloaded the page 1000 times that hits the above code and it resulted in having 1000 connections created.",
